    <item>
      <title>How Infold Games fashioned an open world for Infinity Nikki</title>
      <link>https://n-kase.github.io/rss/posts/post-393/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 10:40:01 +0900</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://n-kase.github.io/rss/posts/post-393/</guid>
      <description>&lt;![CDATA[<h2 id="aiによる要約">AIによる要約
</h2><h3 id="概要と事実">概要と事実
</h3><p>Infold Gamesが開発した『Infinity Nikki』は、ドレスアップ要素を核とするシリーズの第五作目であり、初めてオープンワールド型のRPGアドベンチャーとしてリリースされました。プレイヤーは主人公ニキとその猫の相棒モモを操作し、さまざまな衣装を集めながらパズルを解き、ファンタジー世界「ミラランド」を探索します。衣装にはそれぞれ特殊な能力が付与されており、ジャンプや光のエフェクトなど、細部にわたるアニメーションとライティングが特徴です。開発チームは約800人に及び、ビジュアル面ではGlobal Illuminationなどの先進的なシェーディング技術を駆使しています。本作は2025年のApple Design Award（Visuals and Graphics部門）を受賞し、App Storeのエディターズチョイスにも選出されるなど、高い評価を得ています。</p>
<h3 id="ネットの反応と意見の変遷">ネットの反応と意見の変遷
</h3><p>発表直後、SNSやゲーム関連フォーラムでは、衣装の美麗さや光の表現に対する称賛が多数見られました。特に「ドレスが風に揺れる様子」や「ジュエリーのきらめき」など、細部へのこだわりが話題となり、多くのユーザーが「これまでのモバイルゲームとは異なるクオリティ」と評価しました。一方で、オープンワールド化に伴うアクションや戦闘の軽さについて、従来のドレスアップファンから「もう少しゲーム性が欲しい」という声も上がりました。時間が経つにつれて、ビジュアル面の賞賛は変わらず続く一方で、パズル要素や探索の深さが徐々に認識され、ゲーム性への期待が高まっていく傾向が見られました。全体としては、視覚的なインパクトが最初の関心を引き、その後プレイ感覚への理解が深まるという流れがネット上の議論に現れました。</p>
<h3 id="背景と結論">背景と結論
</h3><p>Infold Gamesはこれまでのニキシリーズで培ったドレスアップのノウハウを基盤に、ゼルダシリーズなどのアクションアドベンチャーからインスピレーションを得て、オープンワールドへの挑戦を決めました。開発陣は衣装の物理シミュレーションや光の表現に徹底的にこだわり、現実の素材をベースとしつつファンタジー的な装飾を加えています。このアプローチにより、モバイルプラットフォームでもコンソール級のビジュアル体験を実現し、業界内での技術的基準を一つ引き上げる結果となりました。今後は、視覚的な魅力とゲームプレイのバランスをさらに調整することで、幅広い層に受け入れられるタイトルへと発展していくことが期待されます。</p>
<p><a class="link" href="https://developer.apple.com/news/?id=9mgkwjnm"  target="_blank" rel="noopener"
    >🔗 元記事を読む</a></p>
<details>
<summary>AI要約用RAWデータ（抽出された元記事テキスト）</summary>
<h2 id="how-infold-games-fashioned-an-open-world-for-infinity-nikki">How Infold Games fashioned an open world for Infinity Nikki
</h2><p>April 3, 2026</p>
<p><img alt="Promotional key art for Infinity Nikki featuring the game’s main character in a red and white archer’s outfit, holding a bow, standing on a wooden bridge beside her small white cat companion. A vibrant fantasy village with waterfalls, colorful banners, and layered cliffside buildings stretches out in the background." loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px" src="/rss/downloaded_images/aee422108107fdcf36bc0f0dba607158.jpeg"></p>
<p><em>Infinity Nikki</em> is a literally glowing example of what video game graphics can be.</p>
<p>The fifth in a series of dress-up titles from Infold Games, <em>Infinity Nikki</em> is also the first to embrace elements of RPG action-adventure. But instead of tracking down weapons and battling bad guys, this installment finds its wide-eyed heroine solving puzzles by collecting enchanted outfits found throughout a series of wondrous lands.</p>
<h3 id="infinity-nikki">Infinity Nikki
</h3><ul>
<li>**Available on:**iPhone, iPad</li>
<li>**Based in:**Shanghai</li>
<li>**Awards:**Apple Design Award winner for Visuals and Graphics (2025), App Store Awards Game of the Year finalist (2025), App Store Editors’ Choice</li>
</ul>
<p><a class="link" href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/infinity-nikki/id6502622570"  target="_blank" rel="noopener"
    >Download Infinity Nikki from the App Store &gt;</a></p>
<p>The fashion-forward gameplay still remains, of course. Nikki’s dress sways and waves every step of the way, while capes sparkle and drift in the wind. Different outfits are imbued with different abilities that allow players to guide Nikki — and her cat companion, Momo — through clever puzzles. And from quaint cobblestone towns to distant mountains, every corner of the game’s Miraland — brought to life with cutting-edge visuals — is awash in beautifully realized lighting and effects from advanced shading techniques like Global Illumination. (Executive producer Kentaro Tominaga previously worked on several installments of the <em>Legend of Zelda</em> series.)</p>
<p>It’s a wonderland of texture, light, and animation — and the <a class="link" href="https://developer.apple.com/design/awards/"  target="_blank" rel="noopener"
    >2025 Apple Design Award winner</a> for Visuals and Graphics. To find out more, we caught up with Douhu, <em>Infinity Nikki’s</em> lead gameplay systems designer for outfits; Ade, lead programmer; and Dodie, art director.</p>
<p><img alt="Viewed from inside a cave opening, a fantasy game character in a white gown hangs from a zipline cable, soaring above a colorful village nestled among rocky cliffs and autumn-colored trees, with a waterfall in the background." loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px" src="/rss/downloaded_images/874df7389f36a65c847049db23348e21.jpeg"></p>
<p><strong>Why did you decide to make this fifth installment an open-world RPG?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Douhu:</strong> When we started thinking about this six years ago, we already knew it would be an open-world game. So we asked ourselves: How do we go about bringing Nikki into that space? And how do we set it apart from other open-world games on the market?</p>
<p>To make these worlds as immersive as we can, we keep an eye on all the details, all the time.</p>
<p>Douhu, lead gameplay systems designer for outfits</p>
<p><strong>This is the first Nikki game to include action-adventure elements and light combat.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Douhu:</strong> Yes, but we knew that combat wouldn’t be part of the game’s core play. The Nikki series has such a defined style. We thought a lot about how to maintain that.</p>
<p><strong>How many people worked on the visuals for this?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Douhu:</strong> Oh, it’s a huge team — roughly 800 people. It’s a fun but a complicated job. We have a lot of visual pipelines all going at once: cutscenes, the NPC ecosystem, lighting, performance. The production complexity is so high.</p>
<p><img alt="A close-up of a highly ornate red and gold garment featuring a brightly colored, embroidered butterfly design on the chest, accented with glowing lights, draped pearls, and large red lotus flowers on the shoulders." loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px" src="/rss/downloaded_images/2e77f5e99dbff8b7cd999eb18171bd89.jpeg"></p>
<p><strong>The payoff for that work seems to be everywhere: The game is full of fabrics, sparkles, environments, and natural elements.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Douhu:</strong> And we think about all of them. For instance, when Nikki runs up a flight of steps in a cutscene, we don’t want her to stamp her feet down. We want her to move lightly and elegantly. All the sounds you hear are based on real-world sounds, though we’ve added some imagination to them in post-production editing. To make these worlds as immersive as we can, we keep an eye on all the details, all the time.</p>
<p><strong>Nikki’s double-jump is especially elegant; it’s almost like a glider coming in for the softest of landings.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Douhu:</strong> That’s because we want players to have plenty of time to experience the world. Our core gameplay is based on jumping, but it’s not a very quick motion. It’s slow, like a micro-response for that specific floating motion. And that’s because we want to let players breathe and appreciate all the details of Miraland.</p>
<p><img alt="A portrait of a fantasy game character wearing an elaborate tall gold filigree crown adorned with red gemstones, with cascading crystal face chains and a sheer veil framing her face. She wears a white lace gown with ruby jewels at the neckline, set against a dark blue twilight sky." loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px" src="/rss/downloaded_images/886420ffbec12de9f317863a463efd7c.jpeg"></p>
<p><strong>What is Day 1 like on the visuals for something like this?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Douhu:</strong> Because this is our fifth game with Nikki, we already have the character and philosophy built out, so those first days are more about sketching out the new world and its different maps.</p>
<p><strong>Ade:</strong> To start, we reconstruct the structure and physical performance of the fabrics in the engine, based mostly on reality. Then we’ll do extreme evolutions on the fabrics. We have so many fabric categories in our library, and a lot of those are heritage from previous titles. But we make all kinds of adjustments, and add all kinds of effects to make the game feel like it’s beyond reality.</p>
<p><strong>Douhu:</strong> We do have a big closet in our office! But we want to emphasize that we’re not just exporting real fabrics or trying to recreate reality. We’re adding layers of fantasy. We add complicated embroideries, more patterns, and glittering special effects to depict a more whimsical, fantastic version of reality. That’s why Nikki’s outfits look more gorgeous than they would in real life. Hopefully!</p>
<p><img alt="A fantasy game character dressed in an elaborate white lace gown and ornate gold crown floats in midair, shooting a beam of golden light from her hand toward a large mechanical wheel. A whimsical village is visible far below." loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px" src="/rss/downloaded_images/ffdc1c3b463917674bdba52bdb0de2b8.jpeg"></p>
<p><strong>Could you select an element in the game and share a little about how it was brought to life?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Dodie:</strong> Color has always been central to our art creation, so I’ll share two examples from Version 2.0: the five-star outfit Behind Prayers and the location called Snail Ranch.</p>
<p>The core design concept of Behind Prayers is ”a confined divine maiden,” so that meant a maximal design approach. The divine maiden longs for freedom, yet she’s draped in heavy layers of ornate garments and gemstones. These represent both sacred glory and the weight of restraint: dazzling and radiant, yet undeniably burdensome.</p>
<p>We chose gold as the primary color to express sanctity and brilliance, and we introduced touches of green to break potential visual monotony. We further embellished the outfit with a rich array of multicolored gemstones and enhanced it with prismatic sparkle effects, allowing it to shimmer vividly — even at night.</p>
<p>Snail Ranch, meanwhile, is the player’s first destination in Itzaland — the place where Nikki first encounters the Shroomlings and the snails.</p>
<p>The lighting in this area is intentionally bright and inviting. Sunlight filters through enormous leaves, creating a warm and relaxing atmosphere, while even small puddles along the path reflect the deep b</p>
<p>&hellip;（長文のため省略されました）</p>
</details>
]]></description>
